-- Cyclist Mark Cavendish Wins BBC Sports Personality of Year Award
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2011-12-22T22:08:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/cyclist-mark-cavendish-wins-bbc-sports-personality-of-year-award.html
Mark Cavendish , who had five stage
wins on this year’s Tour de  France , was named the British
Broadcasting Corp.’s Sports Personality of the Year.  The 26-year-old from the Isle of Man topped a public poll
ahead of British Open golf champion  Darren Clarke  and distance
runner Mo Farrah. He is the second cyclist to win the annual
prize in four years after Chris Hoy in 2008.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  